5. Watchdog Implementation

5.1 Watchdog Architecture

Each conduit has an independent watchdog timer.

```verilog
// conduit_watchdog.v
module conduit_watchdog (
    input clk,
    input reset,
    input start,
    input watchdog_pet,   // Must be asserted within timeout
    output reg fail_safe  // Asserted if watchdog expires
);

parameter TIMEOUT_CYCLES = 1000000;  // 10 ms at 100 MHz

reg [31:0] counter;

always @(posedge clk) begin
    if (reset || start) begin
        counter <= 0;
        fail_safe <= 1'b0;
    end else if (!fail_safe) begin
        if (watchdog_pet) begin
            counter <= 0;  // Reset the watchdog
        end else if (counter < TIMEOUT_CYCLES) begin
            counter <= counter + 1;
        end else begin
            fail_safe <= 1'b1;  // Timeout!
        end
    end
end

endmodule
```

