8. Deployment Checklist

For Zone 0 (ST-T1024 Core):

· ROM burned with immutable "Brutal Facts"
· FSM formal verification completed (TLA+/SPIN)
· AET measured on target hardware (≤ 680 ns)
· SK-1024 update key loaded (hardware-protected)
· Power gating verified (0V idle, <5 ns wake)

For Zone 1 (Certified Bridge):

· FIFO controller validated (no overflow, no data loss)
· Watchdog timers configured for all conduits
· Fail-safe state defined (0V/0% output)
· Translation logic tested against all legacy protocols

For Zone 2 (Legacy OT):

· Conduit rate-limiting configured
· Modbus/DNP3/CAN bus mapping validated
· No reverse path to Zone 0 (hardware-enforced)

For Zone 3 (Human Interface):

· Display only — no control feedback
· Error messages clearly distinguish faults

